The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Tuesday, June 10, 2003 				 Bangsagata
																								Ensembles latest production Bangsagata is a Bengali adaptation of Pidhijat by the eminent Marathi playwright Satish Alekar. The play deals with the dynamics of corruption through generations. In an irreverent tongue-in-the-cheek fashion, the play smoothly swings from reality to what can become reality and back. It explores the new mores of relationship of society and of politics and the future facing the younger generation. Directed by Sohag Sen, the cast includes Tapas Thakur, Dulal Lahiri, Dipak Ghosh, Kaushik Basu, Sandhita Chatterjee and Suchita Roychowdhury.																								When: Today at 7 pm																								Where: Academy of Fine Arts
